        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1957-12-23T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-01-06T10:00:00-05:00" n="235" subtype="editorial-note"
                type="document" xml:id="d235">
                <head>235. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_MADII1">Douglas A. MacArthur II</persName> and
                        <persName>James S. Cottman, Jr.</persName>, of the Executive Secretariat,
                    recorded in a memorandum of conversation, February 2, that they and <persName
                        corresp="#p_LEA1">Ernest A. Lister</persName>, Officer in Charge of United
                    Kingdom and Ireland Affairs, had met on February 1 with Sir <persName
                        corresp="#p_CSHA1">Harold Caccia</persName>, Deputy Under Secretary at the
                    Foreign Office; Sir <persName>Hubert Graves</persName>, British Ambassador in
                    Vietnam; <persName corresp="#p_CJE1">John E. Coulson</persName>, Minister of
                    Embassy in Washington; and Evelyn Shuckburgh, Assistant Under Secretary at the
                    Foreign Office, “to compare notes as to US and UK responsibilities for future
                    actions” resulting from the <persName corresp="#p_ESA1"
                        >Eden</persName>–<persName corresp="#p_EDD1">Eisenhower</persName> talks.
                    (Department of State, Conference Files: Lot 62 D 181, CF 648B) Documentation on
                    their discussions, which confirmed and clarified decisions made from January 30
                    to February 1, is <hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi> On February 4, a summary of the
                        <persName corresp="#p_ESA1">Eden</persName>–<persName corresp="#p_EDD1"
                        >Eisenhower</persName> talks was sent in nearly identical circular telegrams
                    (518 and 519), drafted by <persName corresp="#p_MLT1">Merchant</persName>,
                    approved by <persName corresp="#p_MADII1">Mac-Arthur</persName>, and cleared by
                        <gloss target="#t_NEA1">NEA</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_FE1">FE</gloss>, and
                        <gloss target="#t_ARA1">ARA</gloss>, to London and 49 other posts. (<hi
                        rend="italic">Ibid.,</hi> Central Files, 611.41/2–456)</p>
            </div>
